-- Adani, Hindalco, Sesa Goa and Sterlite Technologies: India Equity Preview
-- Rakteem Katakey
-- 2010-07-21T02:49:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/adani-hindalco-sesa-goa-and-sterlite-technologies-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex , lost
50.28, or 0.3 percent, to 17,878.14. The S&P CNX  Nifty  Index on
the National Stock Exchange dropped 0.3 percent to 5,368. The
 BSE 200 Index  retreated 0.3 percent to 2,278.9. SGX CNX Nifty
Index futures for July delivery gained 0.6 to 5,383 at 10:35 a.m.
in Singapore.  
 Drug-related companies: India filed a case with the World
Trade Organization’s Dispute Settlement Body in Geneva over the
seizure of Indian-made generic drugs by Netherlands, the Hindu
Business line reported, citing a person familiar with the
development.  Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd.  (RBXY IN) dropped 0.7
percent to 446.05 rupees.  Dr. Reddy’s Laboratories Ltd.  (DRRD IN)
decreased 2.9 percent to 1,430.65 rupees.  
 Adani Enterprises Ltd.  (ADE IN): India’s largest non-state
trader of farm goods plans to raise as much as $850 million
selling shares to institutional investors at about 536.15 rupees
apiece, a sale document obtained by Bloomberg News showed. The
shares fell 0.2 percent to 543.80 rupees.  
 BGR Energy Systems Ltd.  (BGRL IN): The maker of equipment
for power, oil and petrochemical industries was rated “buy” in
new coverage by BNP Paribas analysts  Lakshminarayana Ganti  and
 Charanjit Singh . The analysts have a share-price estimate of 908
rupees. The stock lost 0.4 percent to 740.2 rupees.  
 Hindalco Industries Ltd.  (HNDL IN): India’s largest
producer of aluminum said production from its smelter at Hirakud
in the eastern state of Orissa was hampered by bad weather.
Output may decline by 13 percent in the year ending March 31, it
said yesterday in a statement to the Bombay Stock Exchange. The
shares rose 0.1 percent to 152.8 rupees.  
 Sterlite Technologies Ltd.  (SOTL IN): The maker of fiber-
optic cables was raised to “buy” from “hold” by Anubhav
Gupta, an analyst at Kim Eng Securities, with a price estimate
of 125 rupees per share. The stock gained 1.7 percent to 113.85
rupees.  
 Sesa Goa Ltd.  (SESA IN): India’s biggest iron-ore exporter
was downgraded to “reduce” from “add” by Giriraj Daga, an
analyst at Khandwala Securities, with a price estimate of 350
rupees per share. Sesa Goa increased 1.6 percent to 353.85
rupees.  
 Vishal Retail Ltd.  (VISH IN): The Future Group has offered
to buy Vishal Retail Ltd., Mint newspaper said, citing an
unidentified person familiar with the offer. Vishal Retail
chairman  Ram Chandra Agarwal  denied that Future Group made an
offer, the report said.  Kishore Biyani  founder and Chief
Executive officer of Future Group declined to comment, it said.
The stock advanced 1.3 percent to 52.1 rupees.  
